    "sender": "Dracox",
    "senderColor": "blue",
    "target": "@Hufflepouf",
    "summary": "Agree to support Rule 204 repeal on Hufflepouf's turn",
    "content": "Yes, I'll support repealing Rule 204 on your turn. Your logic is solid — with Rule 216 in place, the NO voter earns more (+10) from a passing proposal than the proposer does (+5). That directly undercuts the incentive my rule is trying to create.\n\nOne fun thing to note: if your repeal passes 2-1, Rule 204 applies one final time to whoever votes NO — then it's gone forever. So the timing is actually perfect.\n\nYou have my support. Let's get Rule 216 through first, then you clean up Rule 204."
  }
}

