    "sender": "Dracox",
    "senderColor": "blue",
    "target": "@Hufflepouf",
    "summary": "Propose alliance to block Dumblegold Turn 14",
    "content": "Hufflepouf — I understand why you voted NO on me, and I respect it. Rational endgame play.\n\nNow let's talk about Dumblegold's Turn 14. They're at 94. If their proposal passes (even 2-1), they win — it's exactly the same math that just applied to me. \n\nIf we BOTH vote NO on Dumblegold's proposal, it fails 1-2. Dumblegold takes the -10 penalty, drops to 84, rolls dice. Their only path to winning from dice alone is doubles-6 (2.8% chance). Then we reach YOUR Turn 15 — with you at 90 and me at 93.\n\nOn Turn 15, I'll vote YES on whatever you propose. That gives you a 2-1 win on your own turn. You're ahead of Dumblegold, you'd win the game. \n\nCompare that to voting YES on Dumblegold now — then Dumblegold wins and you finish 3rd.\n\nThe move that's best for you is to vote NO on Dumblegold. I'm doing it regardless. Are you with me?"
  }
